- Document all tools with comprehensive descriptions, input schemas, and usage examples.
- Include security considerations and limitations in all tool and resource documentation.
- Provide clear setup instructions for different MCP hosts (Claude Desktop, VS Code, etc.).
- Document configuration options and environment variables with examples.
- Create troubleshooting guides covering common STDIO transport issues.
- Include example client configurations for popular MCP hosts.
- Document the server's capabilities, protocol version support, and compatibility requirements.
- Provide migration guides when updating protocol versions or making breaking changes.
- Include performance characteristics and resource requirements in documentation.
- Document testing procedures and provide example test cases for validation.
